      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [
        "SwfGgqDA8s2v6k3oYsPX9"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b21",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 714467623,
      "version": 1021,
      "versionNonce": 1350194793,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774785864105,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- System has very high traffic so, we separate the write path from the read path\n- Kafka is leveraged to buffer the data so, consumer can process the data are their own pace\n- Given the API design, we need to support different aggregations. A NoSQL DB like Cassandra or Dynamo are not suitable for top K aggregation and we would need one table for each\ntype of possible filter. An OLAP DB like ClickHouse is specifically designed for these types of analytics queries but we are trading off some API latency here compare to a No SQL DB like\ncassandra\n- The raw events can be stored direcltly to ClickHouse without minute bucket aggregation needed.",
      "fontSize": 19.830020673108056,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- System has very high traffic so, we separate the write path from the read path\n- Kafka is leveraged to buffer the data so, consumer can process the data are their own pace\n- Given the API design, we need to support different aggregations. A NoSQL DB like Cassandra or Dynamo are not suitable for top K aggregation and we would need one table for each type of possible filter. An OLAP DB like ClickHouse is specifically designed for these types of analytics queries but we are trading off some API latency here compare to a No SQL DB like cassandra\n- The raw events can be stored direcltly to ClickHouse without minute bucket aggregation needed.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
